# Git remotes and push target (Dr. Elias clinic)

This workspace is a **monorepo** (`frontend/`, `backend/`). All changes are pushed to a single repository only:

| Area | Remote name | URL | What to push |
|------|-------------|-----|----------------|
| **All project files** (`frontend/`, `backend/`, root files) | `origin` | `https://github.com/yazan-alsamman/clinic.git` | `git push origin main` |

## After you finish a task: always push to `origin`

1. Commit your changes in this repository.
2. Push using:

```bash
git push origin main
```

## Do not

- Do not use subtree split/push workflows.
- Do not push to any remote other than `origin`.
